For general queries not relating to the above, please email
I work with the NHS, Public Health and other organisations across the 33
London boroughs to ensure people with diabetes get the care they need. I
deliver our national campaigns locally working with volunteers and local
groups to ensure we are championing good care and information at a local
My job is to raise the profile of Diabetes UK, its work and the work of our
volunteers and fundraisers in the London media, newspapers, radio and TV – so
please get in touch if you have a story to tell.
I am the first point of contact for the team and assist in the day to day
activities. I arrange health and awareness events across the region, recruit
volunteers for these events, coordinate with the organisers and look after
materials. I am always on the end of the phone for any enquiries.
My role is to create and lead volunteering development plans across the
Region. I develop and drive volunteering growth plans and ensure volunteering
operates and develops in line with best practice and policy.
I’m the first point of contact for individual volunteers and Local Groups in
London. I help to recruit and train new volunteers, together with training and
### Regional Fundraiser - London and South East
I work closely with our Volunteering Team to support all our Volunteers,
specifically roles that include fundraising. I look forward to meeting as many
of you as possible during my time here.
